## Module-by-Module Analysis

### 1. JSX Bridge (config.js) â›” SEVERITY: EXTREME

**Location:** `splice-cep/panel/js/config.js:212-247`

#### CRITICAL Issue: No Timeout on evalScript()

**Impact:** Complete UI freeze if ExtendScript hangs. Affects ALL 24+ jsx.call() sites.

**Root Cause:**
```javascript
evalScript: async function(script) {
    await this.ensureInitialized();

    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        this.cs.evalScript(script, (result) => {
            // âŒ NO TIMEOUT - Promise never rejects if ExtendScript hangs!
            resolve(result);
        });
    });
}
```

**Trace Path:**
1. User clicks GO button â†’ `runDetection()` calls `jsx.call('exportSequenceAudioForAnalysis')`
2. ExtendScript calls Premiere Pro export API
3. **IF** Premiere hangs (rendering, large file, disk I/O): callback never fires
4. Promise never resolves â†’ UI frozen â†’ Button disabled permanently

**Scenarios That Trigger:**
- Premiere Pro busy (rendering, exporting)
- ExtendScript infinite loop (bug in hostScript.jsx)
- Slow operations (large file I/O, network calls in JSX)
- Modal dialogs in Premiere (blocks ExtendScript)
- System under load (ExtendScript thread starved)

**Fix Required:**
```javascript
evalScript: async function(script) {
    await this.ensureInitialized();
    const EVALSCRIPT_TIMEOUT = 30000; // 30 seconds

    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        let completed = false;

        const timeoutId = setTimeout(() => {
            if (!completed) {
                completed = true;
                reject(new Error(`ExtendScript timeout after ${EVALSCRIPT_TIMEOUT}ms: ${script.substring(0, 100)}...`));
            }
        }, EVALSCRIPT_TIMEOUT);

        this.cs.evalScript(script, (result) => {
            if (completed) {
                console.warn('[JSX] Late evalScript result received after timeout');
                return;
            }

            completed = true;
            clearTimeout(timeoutId);

            // ... existing error handling ...
            resolve(result);
        });
    });
},
```

**Configurable Timeouts:**
```javascript
const EVALSCRIPT_TIMEOUTS = {
    DEFAULT: 30000,        // 30s - most operations
    QUICK: 5000,           // 5s  - checkSequenceOpen, getVersion
    NORMAL: 30000,         // 30s - getClips, createMarker
    LONG: 120000,          // 2m  - export operations, large file I/O
    CRITICAL: 300000       // 5m  - complex timeline operations
};
```

**Affected Call Sites:** All 24+ occurrences in main.js
- `checkSequenceOpen()` - every GO button press
- `getActiveSequence()` - frequent calls
- `getClipsInTrack()` - analysis operations
- `createMarker()` - loops (100+ times for captions)
- `razorSequenceAtSeconds()` - each cut
- `exportSequenceAudioForAnalysis()` - can take 60+ seconds
- `buildSequenceFromCutList()` - complex timeline rebuild

**Fix Estimate:** 3-4 hours
**Test Plan:** Full regression suite in `CRITICAL_JSX_BRIDGE_TIMEOUT_BUG.md`

---

### 2. Music Generation (music.js) â›” SEVERITY: EXTREME

**Location:** `splice-cep/panel/js/music.js`

#### 5 CRITICAL Issues + 12 HIGH Issues

#### CRITICAL #1: Polling Interval Memory Leak (Lines 872-917)

**Impact:** Server overload, browser crash after 100 rapid operations

**Root Cause:**
```javascript
// Clears interval but callback still executes
if (musicState.variationsPollingInterval) {
  clearInterval(musicState.variationsPollingInterval);
}

musicState.variationsPollingInterval = setInterval(async () => {
  if (musicState.currentVariationsJobId !== jobId) {
    return; // Band-aid - interval still runs
  }
  // ... polling logic ...
}, MUSIC_POLL_INTERVAL);
```

**Why It Breaks:**
- `clearInterval()` stops scheduling new callbacks but doesn't cancel in-flight async operations
- Rapid variation generation creates multiple concurrent intervals
- After 100 clicks: **100 intervals Ã— 5s = 500 network requests every 5 seconds**

**Fix:** Add AbortController for request cancellation
```javascript
let variationsAbortController = null;

function startPollingVariations(jobId) {
  // Cancel previous polling
  if (variationsAbortController) {
    variationsAbortController.abort();
  }

  if (musicState.variationsPollingInterval) {
    clearInterval(musicState.variationsPollingInterval);
  }

  variationsAbortController = new AbortController();
  musicState.currentVariationsJobId = jobId;

  musicState.variationsPollingInterval = setInterval(async () => {
    try {
      const status = await getVariationsStatus(jobId, variationsAbortController.signal);
      // ... handle status ...
    } catch (err) {
      if (err.name === 'AbortError') return; // Cancelled, ignore
      console.error('[Music] Poll error:', err);
    }
  }, MUSIC_POLL_INTERVAL);
}
```

**Fix Estimate:** 2 hours

---

#### CRITICAL #2: Audio Player Not Disposed (Lines 1045-1047)

**Impact:** 2GB memory leak after 100 previews, browser crashes

**Root Cause:**
```javascript
if (!musicState.variationPlayers[index]) {
  musicState.variationPlayers[index] = new Audio();
  musicState.variationPlayers[index].addEventListener('ended', () => {
    btn.textContent = 'Play';
  });
}
```

**Why It Breaks:**
- Each `new Audio()` allocates 10-50MB (MediaElement + decoder buffers)
- Event listeners never removed
- Setting `src = ''` stops playback but doesn't free decoder resources

**Fix:** Proper cleanup
```javascript
function disposeAudioPlayers() {
  musicState.variationPlayers.forEach(player => {
    if (player) {
      player.pause();
      player.removeEventListener('ended', handleEnded); // Remove all listeners
      player.src = '';
      player.load(); // Force resource release
    }
  });
  musicState.variationPlayers = [];
}

// Call on panel close or variation change
```

**Fix Estimate:** 1 hour

---

#### CRITICAL #3: DOM Thrashing in Loops (Lines 1167-1178)

**Impact:** 500ms UI freeze every 5 seconds during polling

**Root Cause:**
```javascript
container.innerHTML = musicState.jobs.map(job => `
  <div class="music-job-item">...</div>
`).join('');
```

**Fix:** Use DocumentFragment + requestAnimationFrame
```javascript
function renderJobsList() {
  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    const fragment = document.createDocumentFragment();

    musicState.jobs.forEach(job => {
      const item = document.createElement('div');
      item.className = 'music-job-item';
      item.textContent = job.name; // Use textContent, not innerHTML
      fragment.appendChild(item);
    });

    container.replaceChildren(fragment); // Atomic replacement
  });
}
```

**Fix Estimate:** 1 hour

---

#### CRITICAL #4: No Timeout on Network Requests (Lines 138-142, 393-404)

**Impact:** 10-minute requests can't be cancelled, server exhaustion

**Root Cause:**
```javascript
const response = await fetchFn(`${backendUrl}/music/generate-timeline`, {
  ...
}, 600000); // 10 MINUTES with no cancellation
```

**Fix:** Add AbortController
```javascript
let timelineAbortController = null;

async function handleTimelineConfirm() {
  if (timelineAbortController) {
    timelineAbortController.abort();
  }

  timelineAbortController = new AbortController();

  const response = await fetchFn(`${backendUrl}/music/generate-timeline`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify({}),
    signal: timelineAbortController.signal
  }, 600000);
}
```

**Fix Estimate:** 2 hours (all network calls)

---

#### CRITICAL #5: Event Listener Duplication (Lines 519-561)

**Impact:** 60 concurrent requests after 20 tab switches, server DDoS

**Root Cause:**
```javascript
function setupMusicEventListeners() {
  document.addEventListener('input', (e) => { ... });
  document.addEventListener('click', (e) => { ... });
  document.addEventListener('change', (e) => { ... });
}
// Called on EVERY navigation to music section
```

**Fix:** Add listener guards
```javascript
let listenersInitialized = false;

function setupMusicEventListeners() {
  if (listenersInitialized) return;
  listenersInitialized = true;

  // ... add listeners once ...
}
```

**Fix Estimate:** 30 minutes

---

**Total Music Module Fix Time:** ~6-8 hours
**Priority:** Fix before launch (memory leaks will crash production users)

