## Testing Requirements

### Regression Tests (Must Pass)

1. **JSX Timeout Test** - Verify timeout fires after 30s
2. **Memory Leak Test** - Run 100 music generations, verify <200MB growth
3. **UI Responsiveness Test** - Apply 100 captions, verify <5s completion
4. **Race Condition Test** - Double-click analyze, verify single operation
5. **Auth Persistence Test** - Rapid API calls, verify single token refresh

### Load Testing

- **Concurrent Users:** 100 simultaneous users
- **Duration:** 1 hour sustained load
- **Operations:** All AI features (music, captions, reframe, multitrack)
- **Success Criteria:** No crashes, <10% error rate, <3s p95 response time

### Performance Budgets

| Operation | Target | Acceptable | Failure |
|-----------|--------|-----------|---------|
| Panel Init | <2s | <5s | >10s |
| Sequence Detection | <500ms | <1s | >2s |
| Caption Apply (100) | <5s | <10s | >15s |
| Music Generation | <30s | <60s | >120s |
| Analysis Start | <1s | <3s | >5s |

---

## Prevention Measures

### Code Review Checklist

- [ ] All `jsx.call()` wrapped in timeout
- [ ] All `setInterval()` cleaned up in finally
- [ ] All network requests use AbortController
- [ ] All DOM loops use requestAnimationFrame
- [ ] All state flags reset in finally blocks
- [ ] All async operations have timeout parameter
- [ ] All event listeners have cleanup path

### Automated Checks

- ESLint rule: `no-unhandled-promise-rejection`
- ESLint rule: `no-infinite-promise` (custom)
- Performance budget: Fail CI if operation >100ms
- Memory budget: Fail CI if heap growth >100MB per operation

### Monitoring

```javascript
// Add to all critical operations
const perfStart = performance.now();
try {
  await criticalOperation();
} finally {
  const duration = performance.now() - perfStart;
  if (duration > 100) {
    logSlowOperation('criticalOperation', duration);
  }
}
```

